-- FDP Delayed Support for Euro Bonds, Westerwelle Tells Focus
-- B y   R a i n e r   B u e r g i n
-- 2012-08-05T11:27:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-05/fdp-delayed-support-for-euro-bonds-westerwelle-tells-focus.html
Chancellor  Angela Merkel ’s government
would have supported the introduction of so-called euro bonds
earlier if it hadn’t been for the Free Democratic Party’s
refusal to back such a move, German Foreign Minister  Guido Westerwelle , a former FDP chairman, told Germany’s  Focus 
magazine.  To contact the reporter on this story:
